.TH pwconv 1M "9 Mar 1993" "SunOS 5.11" "System Administration Commands"
.SH NAME
pwconv \- installs and updates /etc/shadow with information from
/etc/passwd
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
.nf
\fBpwconv\fR
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
.LP
The
.B pwconv
command creates and updates
.B /etc/shadow
with
information from
.BR /etc/passwd .
.sp
.LP
\fBpwconv\fR relies on a special value of 'x' in the password field of
\fB/etc/passwd.\fR This value of 'x' indicates that the password for the user
is already in
.B /etc/shadow
and should not be modified.
.sp
.LP
If the
.B /etc/shadow
file does not exist, this command will create
\fB/etc/shadow\fR with information from
.BR /etc/passwd .
The command
populates
.B /etc/shadow
with the user's login name, password, and
password aging information. If password aging information does not exist in
\fB/etc/passwd\fR for a given user, none will be added to  \fB/etc/shadow\fR.
However, the last changed information will always be updated.
.sp
.LP
If the 
.B /etc/shadow
file does exist, the following tasks will be
performed:
.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fR
.ad
.sp .6
.RS 4n
Entries that are in the 
.B /etc/passwd
file and not in the
\fB/etc/shadow\fR file will be added to the \fB/etc/shadow\fR file.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fR
.ad
.sp .6
.RS 4n
Entries that are in the 
.B /etc/shadow
file and not in the
\fB/etc/passwd\fR file will be removed from \fB/etc/shadow\fR.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fR
.ad
.sp .6
.RS 4n
Password attributes (for example, password and aging information)  that
exist in an
.B /etc/passwd
entry will be moved to the corresponding entry
in
.BR /etc/shadow .
.RE

.sp
.LP
The
.B pwconv
command can only be used by the super-user.
.SH FILES
.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.B /etc/opasswd
.ad
.RS 16n
.rt

.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.B /etc/oshadow
.ad
.RS 16n
.rt

.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.B /etc/passwd
.ad
.RS 16n
.rt

.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.B /etc/shadow
.ad
.RS 16n
.rt

.RE

.SH ATTRIBUTES
.sp
